module.description: This is top module of SYS0 for LOKI

register.description: Description Register. This register provides IP module ID, revision information, instance index and standard MMR registers offset.

bitfield.description: Module identifier used to uniquely identify this IP.

Standard IP MMR block offset. Standard IP MMRs are the set of from aggregated IRQ registers till DTB.
0: Standard IP MMRs do not exist
0x1-0xF: Standard IP MMRs begin at offset of (64*STDIPOFF from the base IP address)
IP Instance ID number. If multiple instances of IP exist in the device, this field can identify the instance number (0-15).
Major revision of IP (0-15).
Minor revision of IP (0-15).

register.description: Extended Description Register. This register provides configuration details of the IP to software drivers and end users.

bitfield.description: Total number of trim bits

register.description: Global Lock Register. Locks registers in both mutable and immutable sections

bitfield.description:
When LOCK is set, write access to registers in mutable and immutable sections are not allowed. Registers in mutable section can be temporarily unlocked by writing the KEY to MUNLOCK.KEY
Following immutable registers are locked by GLOCK.LOCK TESTCFG I2VCFG TSENSCFG LPCMPCFG TIMMUTE0 TIMMUTE1 TIMMUTE2 PARTID LIFECYC

bitenum.token: Global Lock is set
bitenum.description: Global Lock is set

bitenum.token: No effect
bitenum.description: No effect

register.description: Unlocks registers in mutable section

bitfield.description: Write the unlock key 0xC5AF_6927 to temporarily unlock registers in mutable section. The lock is set automatically if no write accesses, to the mutable section, are detected for consecutive 32 CLKULL (24MHz) clock cycles. Writing any value other that the unlock key will immediately lock the mutable register space for write access.

register.description: Lock Status Register

bitfield.description: Lock status of registers in mutable section.

bitenum.token: Registers in the mutable section are locked for write
bitenum.description: Registers in the mutable section are locked for write

bitenum.token: Registers in the mutable section are not locked, and are writable
bitenum.description: Registers in the mutable section are not locked, and are writable

bitfield.description: Status of Global lock

register.description: TMUTE0 trim Register

bitfield.description: SOCADC: Lower 32 bits of CDAC trim. These bits are used in DTC.

register.description: TMUTE1 trim Register

bitfield.description: SOCADC: Middle 32 bits of CDAC trim. These bits are used in DTC.

register.description: TMUTE2 trim Register

bitfield.description: LPCOMP: Bias current trim, 250nA to be terminated across I2V, 1M ohm setting. Resulting target trim voltage 250mV.
ADC REFBUF trim bits.
SOC ADC: Latch trim bits. These bits are used in the analog IP.
SOCADC: Offset trim bits. These bits are used in DTC.
SOCADC: Resistor trim bits. These bits are used in the analog IP.
SOCADC: Upper 2 bits of CDAC trim. These bits are used in DTC.

register.description: TMUTE3 trim Register

bitfield.description: BATMON: Battery calculation coefficient 1
BATMON: Battery calculation coefficient 0
BATMON: Temperature calculation coefficient 2
BATMON: Temperature calculation coefficient 1
BATMON: Temperature calculation coefficient 0

register.description: TMUTE4 trim Register

bitfield.description: PMUREG: Recharge comparator reference level. Valid values are 0x2 to 0xA. Recommended default value is 0x9. Setting 0x2 corresponds to VDDR = 1.35V and 0xA corresponds to VDDR = 1.47V with 15mV linear increase for every step.
BATMON: IO drive strength conversion parameter for the second stage
BATMON: IO drive strength conversion parameter for the first stage
IOC: Maximum IO drive strength
IOC: Medium IO drive strength
IOC: Minimum IO drive strength
DCDC: Set DCDC load current threshold
DCDC: Set inductor peak current
DCDC: Dead time trim
DCDC: Control NMOS switch strength
DCDC: Control PMOS switch strength

register.description: TMUTE5 trim Register

bitfield.description: DCDC: Driver drive strength configuration
GLDO current source trim clear value
GLDO current source trim set value
Software should not rely on the value of a reserved. Writing any other value than the reset value may result in undefined behavior.
